parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine gasket can cause a sudden loss of coolant, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially a loss of visibility due to steam fog, which can increase the risk of accidents.
The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake does not engage or disengage properly
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked on an incline
the parking brake pedal or lever feels soft or spongy
the parking brake warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Side Front Door Latch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side front door latch can cause the door to open while the vehicle is in motion, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's side front door will not latch properly
the door is difficult to close
the door makes a loud noise when closing.
